ZH: 他总是瞧不起别人的能力。
EN: He always looks down on others' abilities.

ZH: 她瞧不起穷人。
EN: She looks down on poor people.

ZH: 他瞧不起那些没有受过高等教育的人。
EN: He looks down on those who haven't received higher education.

ZH: 他瞧不起工人阶级。
EN: He looks down on the working class.

ZH: 她瞧不起自己的长相。
EN: She looks down on her own appearance.

ZH: 他瞧不起自己的家庭背景。
EN: He looks down on his own family background.

ZH: 我很生气，因为他瞧不起我的意见。
EN: I am angry because he looks down on my opinion.

ZH: 她瞧不起那些没有上过大学的人。
EN: She looks down on those who haven't attended college.

ZH: 老板总是瞧不起他的员工。
EN: The boss always looks down on his employees.

ZH: 孩子们瞧不起那个新来的同学。
EN: The children look down on the new classmate.

ZH: 他瞧不起那个国家的文化。
EN: He looks down on the culture of that country.

ZH: 她不应该瞧不起身材矮小的人。
EN: She shouldn't look down on people with short stature.

ZH: 经理总是瞧不起留学生们的英语水平。
EN: The manager always looks down on the English level of international students.

ZH: 我不能容忍别人瞧不起我的家乡。
EN: I can't tolerate others looking down on my hometown.

ZH: 有些人经常瞧不起别人的职业选择。
EN: Some people often look down on others' career choices.

ZH: 他瞧不起那个行业的从业者。
EN: He looks down on professionals in that industry.

ZH: 学校里的部分同学瞧不起外国学生。
EN: Some classmates at school look down on foreign students.

ZH: 她的家人瞧不起她选择的专业。
EN: Her family looks down on the major she has chosen.

ZH: 父母不应该瞧不起他们的孩子们选择的道路。
EN: Parents shouldn't look down on the path their children have chosen.

ZH: 我们不能瞧不起弱势群体。
EN: We should not look down on vulnerable groups.
